164
00:14:36,716 --> 00:14:40,016
Quite the jig ye have danced back at the tavern.

165
00:14:40,816 --> 00:14:44,916
Was it to charm people or to scare away crows? I couldn't tell.

166
00:14:45,216 --> 00:14:50,016
A brazen stone to cast when none would countenance you without your magic.

167
00:14:50,816 --> 00:14:53,016
You're both very charming.

168
00:14:53,616 --> 00:14:56,016
But not as lovely as Namu.

169
00:14:56,516 --> 00:14:56,816
Huh?

170
00:14:56,816 --> 00:14:58,316
Lovely you say?

171
00:14:58,716 --> 00:15:00,016
Is the moon not beautiful...

172
00:15:00,024 --> 00:15:01,024
...for tonight.

173
00:15:01,344 --> 00:15:03,524
Although, we ought not linger.

174
00:15:03,924 --> 00:15:09,324
Rumor has it that an evil hag liveth in these parts.

175
00:15:09,674 --> 00:15:13,524
And naught whets her appetite like the flesh of adventurers.

176
00:15:16,874 --> 00:15:19,524
Thou art hiding something, we thinks.

177
00:15:20,124 --> 00:15:23,024
What dost thou not want us to know about these woods?

178
00:15:23,824 --> 00:15:26,024
Tell us more about this hag.

179
00:15:26,524 --> 00:15:30,024
Aye, a frightful yarn doth excite my spirit!

180
00:15:30,824 --> 00:15:33,524
Ugh, can't you all see she speaks false?

181
00:15:35,324 --> 00:15:36,524
Ahem!

182
00:15:37,324 --> 00:15:39,824
Gumi and her friend Darla

183
00:15:39,824 --> 00:15:42,524
were adventurers who gathered fruit in these woods.

184
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:46,524
Gumi had heard of a trove of berries hidden deep in the forest,

185
00:15:46,524 --> 00:15:51,024
so they ventured in and found a grove untouched by man or beast.

186
00:15:51,024 --> 00:15:54,024
They began picking the berries in pure bliss.

187
00:15:54,024 --> 00:16:00,024
